      "text": "One issue that surfaces with regularity in studies on the problem of organic generation in the early modern period is the battle waged between preexistence theorists and advocates of epigenesis.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU2": {
      "text": "By preexistence, I mean the theory that, at the Creation, God preformed (to some degree at least) every living organism that would ever exist.",
      "label": "premise"
